endemo2.utility.prediction_models.Timeseries¶

class Timeseries(data, calculation_type, rate_of_change=0.0)[source]¶

Bases: object

A Timeseries holds information about a process’ values from the past and provides projections into the future.

Parameters:

  • data ([(<class 'float'>, <class 'float'>)]) – The historical data given for this timeseries.

  • calculation_type (ForecastMethod) – The forecast method, that should be used.

  • rate_of_change – The manually given rate of change for the exponential forecast method.

Variables:

  • _data ([(float, float)]) – The historical data for this timeseries.

  • _coef (Coef) – All the coefficients for different forecast methods.

  • _calculation_type (ForecastMethod) – The currently selected forecast method that should be used for projections.

get_value(target_x)[source]¶

Get the y-axis value for a certain target_x. Combines historical data and prediction data. When historical data is available it is used. When not, a prognosis is made instead.

Parameters:
